title: Want To Buy:  Important question about a law
postcontent:
I would like some factual based answers to a question. I DO NOT want opinions. If you're a lawyer, even better. 

What is the legal age to buy/own/possess a handgun in the state of Illinois? I'm asking for the age of a private party transaction, not through an FFL. The federal age for private party is 18.

Here's where it gets confusing, Illinois has an age limit on foid cards (21), unless you have parental consent. I've read through the statutes concerning this matter, and my interpretation is that >18 but <21 may own, possess, and purchase any type of firearm through a private party transaction. Of course, records will be kept, waiting periods as well. 

Please, if you have some factual based evidence that would help me in this matter, please let me know. If you attempt to be rude or uncivil, I'll just ignore it.

Ps. Calling the ISP or DNR gets you nowhere. Some say they don't know, some say 21, some 18. When asked to provide some proof or statute support, no one has time for you. Our state is a joke when it comes to legal firearm owners.

title: For Sale:  Brand New in Box Del-Ton Sport!
postcontent:
This rifle is BNIB and comes with one brand new D&H 30 round magazine.

You can read a review of this model here: GunBlast.com Review 

The DT Sport proved to be one hundred percent reliable, as expected. The carbine fed, fired, and ejected every cartridge perfectly. Accuracy was excellent, especially considering the mil-spec trigger. I do much better work with a match trigger, such as the Alexander or Timney, but this carbine is built for fighting, and the trigger is well-suited to that task. The AR-15 is a wonderful concept, and Del-Ton executes it very well. The Del-Ton rifles are built very well, and just because the DT Sport is one of the most affordable AR-15 carbines available, does not mean that it sacrifices on quality. The DT Sport has everything that you need, and nothing that you don’t. It performs as well as rifles costing three times the price, and buying a basic rifle such as this leaves a lot more cash to purchase a good optic, plenty of extra magazines, and ammunition. You can’t have too much ammunition. The stuff keeps well, needs no refrigeration, and several thousand rounds will fit neatly under your bed. Buy it while you still can.

Also spec info easily found here:

http://www.del-ton.com/DT_Sport_p/dtsport.htm

Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  IWI Tavor FDE
postcontent: IWI Tavor Bullpup rifle in Flat Dark Earth (FDE/Brown) color. Uses standard AR mags. Winner of this auction will also be able to buy optics, ammo, etc at a discounted price. Please contact us if you have any questions. Please see following from IWI website.... At the end of the 1982 Israel-Lebanon War arose an understanding that the modern battlefield had changed. One of the conclusions from the war, particularly relevant to the small arms industry, was that the battle had moved from open field conflicts to close-quarters engagements – and there was a need for a seamless transition from daylight to nighttime capability on a single mission. Out of this understanding, and after more than a decade of collaboration and testing with the Israel Defense Forces (IDF) - the TAVOR rifle was born. Just as race car technology trickles down to consumer automobiles, so do these time and battle-tested firearms now become a modern sporting rifle platform for civilian gun enthusiasts. The TAVOR is a perfect fusion of an ordnance grade steel receiver coupled to a Mil-Spec cold hammer forged barrel and encased into a high-impact strength polymer uni-body with exceptional situational ergonomics. The ultra-compact form factor allows for easy transitions in close quarter situations…or even in your favorite deer blind. The bullpup design moves the center of gravity of the rifle closer to the users’ body allowing for more instinctive aiming and improved acquisition time to target. This innovative design also allows for a full length barrel, which means no loss of down range ballistic accuracy. Near and far range accuracy is enhanced by the minimized recoil provided by a non-lubricated long stroke gas piston system. With the exception of a hand-specific locking bolt, the rifle is completely ambidextrous allowing for easy left-hand conversion of the operating handle, ejection port, fire-control safety, sling swivel receptacles and fore-mounted accessory Picatinny rail. The TAVOR is supplied with IDF-tested and approved magazines – but you can also use your own AR-15/M16 style magazines

title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense’s 300 Blackout
postcontent: Daniel Defense’s 300 Blackout, was originally designed to give the shooter a 30 caliber projectile which could be fired out of the AR platform without an increase in magazine size while still utilizing a standard bolt. The 300 Blackout is 7.62x35mm which gives the shooter similar ballistic qualities as the .308 and the 7.62x39mm, the AK round, without having to give up the light weight 5.56mm/AR platform. The 300 Blackout can still utilize standard AR magazines without a reduction in magazine capacity. Unlike the 7.62x39mm, the 300 Blackout cartridge is still light on the shoulder with similar recoil to the 5.56mm. The 300 Blackout is designed to be shot suppressed and un-surpressed utilizing various type of super sonic and sub sonic ammunitions

I have a the newer version of Colt's Delta Elite 10mm Brand New in Box, Never fired! The 10mm seems to be really making a comeback in popularity with ballistics more impressive than the 45ACP.

Comes with 2 mags and everything you would expect to receive as new.

You know having one of these is on your list, so get it now while you can still find them new since I believe Colt has also stopped making this newer version as well.

At this point since I am just listing it, I do not want to ship out of state right now and go through the hassle so local FTF transaction only.

Price is $1500 FIRM  Now this is a pet peeve of mine. I put FIRM, yet still get people offering less.  I will not respond to these offers at all!!!

Now, I did not just pull a random number out of head for a price.  I found about 4 or 5 of the exact same model brand new over the last 2 months and monitored the auction price on gunauction.com.  Some started a .01 with 30 bids usually ending at almost exactly $1500 and others with a starting price higher with a sale price again at almost or at $1500 and others simply put a flat rate for "Buy it Now" for $1500 and every single one sold.  So I know this is what I can get.  It would cost me probably $20 for gunauction's sellers fees, but it wouls cost the buyer who almost always pays for sellers FFL to ship it out which includes my FFL's fee and shipping which the price varies between $40 and $60 depending if you get insurance.  Then you have to pay about $25 to $40 for your FFL to receive the gun and then if you use a credit card almost everyone charges 3% for that.  So all these people paying the $1500 on gunauction after all fees are auctually paying $1600 or more.  So that is how I got my price.  No shipping and waiting and hoping it doesn't get damaged.

I do not need to sell. Obviously I prefer a straight green cash money sale!!!! title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant Trigger
postcontent:
Mosin Nagant fully adjustable trigger and extras. 
Ok; guys here’s what I have. This is a standard Mosin Nagant Trigger that has been accurized by creating a fully adjustable and tuneable set screw into the trigger. After searching and searching. After buying parts after parts I finally figured it out. After much trial and error here is the full and best way to accurize your rifle.  Included are all the other necessary items to completely transform that crappy creepy long hard pull of the Mosin Trigger into the shortest crispest and butter smooth trigger you can put on the gun. 
What do you get?
1-	Original issue trigger that has been altered to take a set screw allowing you to have a fully adjustable trigger with friction reducing performance.
2-	Set screw (already installed) this makes your trigger fully adjustable keeping that smooth action. 
3-	Spring. This keeps the trigger in the correct position while not actively being used. It also creates a two stage trigger. When you pull you will feel when the trigger engages. The next bit of pull and BANG. 
4-	Washers (3). Used as a spacer between the sear and the rifles receiver this sets the sear in a better position for a shorter trigger pull. Mix and match to get the best position for the sear and trigger combination for your rifle.  
Guys this is all you need to take one of the most accurate guns in the world and turn it into the most pleasurable gun in the world to shoot. This helps with accuracy and with pulling off target due to a slow long hard creep trigger.
